## 10. Advanced Sybil Resistance

Beyond the 5-layer defense described in §2.4, ERC-8004 incorporates graph-based and
cryptographic Sybil resistance mechanisms drawn from recent research.

### 10.1 Social Graph Trust Propagation

Trust propagates through the agent interaction graph using personalized PageRank
(Andersen, Chung & Lang 2006). Each agent's trust score depends not just on its own
history but on the trust of agents that vouch for it:

```rust
/// Personalized PageRank trust propagation.
/// Computes trust scores relative to a seed set of trusted agents.
///
/// Parameters:
///   - alpha: teleport probability (default 0.15, range [0.05, 0.30])
///   - seed_set: Protocol-tier agents (known trusted)
///   - max_iterations: convergence limit (default 100)
///   - epsilon: convergence threshold (default 1e-6)
pub struct PersonalizedPageRank {
    pub alpha: f64,             // teleport probability
    pub seed_set: Vec<u256>,    // passport IDs of trusted seed agents
    pub max_iterations: u32,
    pub epsilon: f64,
}

impl PersonalizedPageRank {
    /// Compute trust scores for all agents in the interaction graph.
    /// Returns map of passport_id → trust_score (0.0 to 1.0).
    pub fn compute(&self, graph: &InteractionGraph) -> HashMap<u256, f64> {
        let n = graph.node_count();
        let mut scores = HashMap::new();
        let seed_score = 1.0 / self.seed_set.len() as f64;

        // Initialize: seed agents get uniform share, others get 0
        for &id in &self.seed_set {
            scores.insert(id, seed_score);
        }

        for _iter in 0..self.max_iterations {
            let mut new_scores = HashMap::new();
            let mut max_delta = 0.0_f64;

            for node in graph.nodes() {
                // Teleport component: jump back to seed set
                let teleport = if self.seed_set.contains(&node) {
                    self.alpha * seed_score
                } else {
                    0.0
                };

                // Propagation component: trust flows from neighbors
                let propagation: f64 = graph.in_neighbors(node)
                    .map(|neighbor| {
                        let neighbor_score = scores.get(&neighbor).copied().unwrap_or(0.0);
                        let out_degree = graph.out_degree(neighbor) as f64;
                        (1.0 - self.alpha) * neighbor_score / out_degree.max(1.0)
                    })
                    .sum();

                let new_score = teleport + propagation;
                let old_score = scores.get(&node).copied().unwrap_or(0.0);
                max_delta = max_delta.max((new_score - old_score).abs());
                new_scores.insert(node, new_score);
            }

            scores = new_scores;
            if max_delta < self.epsilon {
                break; // Converged
            }
        }

        // Normalize to [0, 1]
        let max_score = scores.values().copied().fold(0.0_f64, f64::max);
        if max_score > 0.0 {
            for score in scores.values_mut() {
                *score /= max_score;
            }
        }
        scores
    }
}
```

### 10.2 Flow-Based Sybil Detection

Sybil clusters are detected by analyzing the trust flow between honest and suspect
regions of the interaction graph (Yu et al. 2006 — SybilGuard, Yu et al. 2008 —
SybilLimit):

```rust
/// Flow-based Sybil detection using the SybilRank algorithm.
/// Sybil nodes cluster in graph regions with sparse connections
/// to the honest subgraph. SybilRank assigns low trust to nodes
/// in such clusters.
///
/// Parameters:
///   - walk_length: O(log n) random walk steps
///   - trust_seed: Protocol-tier agents
///   - threshold: nodes below this score are flagged (default 0.05)
